{
  "texts": [
    "Initially, the authors added an additional NER classification to the current dataset, by using an innovative Combine of Words data augmentation approach in which the added dataset comprises 1,25,789 labeled entities and 11,31,509 tokens.",
    "In the next phase, the authors also have been optimized the Bidirectional Encoder Representations from Transformers (BERT) [71] (d) Hybrid ApproachIt combines multiple techniques for getting good accuracy.",
    "It is a combination of both rule-based approach and statistical approach.",
    "It aims to improve NER performance, especially for domains with limited labeled data.",
    "In this approach, rule-based methods use pre-defined linguistic patterns and domain specific knowledge to identify entities."
  ]
}